## How it all fits together

### Directory structure after `npm run build:java`
```
thymeleaf-basic-preview-vscode/
├── bin/
│   └── thymeleaf-cli.jar        ← built by Maven shade plugin
├── java/
│   ├── pom.xml
│   └── CliTemplateProcessor.java
├── src/
│   └── extension.ts
└── out/
    └── extension.js
```

### Build steps

```bash
# 1. Build the fat JAR (requires Maven + JDK 17+)
npm run build:java

# 2. Compile TypeScript
npm run compile

# 3. Package the VSIX (does both automatically)
npm run package
```

### Runtime decision flow

```
openPreview triggered
        │
        ▼
  bin/thymeleaf-cli.jar exists?
  AND matching .json file exists?
        │
   YES  │  NO
        │   └──→ JS fallback processor (built-in)
        ▼
  java -jar thymeleaf-cli.jar
    --template-path <file.html>
    --data-path     <file.json>
        │
        ▼
  Real Thymeleaf 3 output → WebView
```

The toolbar badge shows **☕ Java** when the real engine is used and **🟨 JS Fallback** when falling back, so you always know which engine rendered the preview.

